snippet.textDisplay: the defense that you are describing is a box and one or diamond and one and has been around since the 1930s. It was and is designed to take the ball out of the primary scorer's hands. When you have a super fast and active player like van vleet at the front of the diamond to initiate the double team, it is especially effective.  This will work well in the playoffs, because the role players can step up for one game but not seven. The reason that you haven't seen it is because Nurse is a very creative coach who is not afraid of public or peer ridicule. He has a deep understanding of the core principles of basketball, and will positively  influence the game  going forward.

snippet.textDisplay: Kawaii needs to watch MJ's triple threat tutorial. MJ was the most triple teamed player ever and had to learn how to get through it.
